00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:33,780
 I hate when they take my $2 million from me.

566
00:26:33,780 --> 00:26:35,500
 But they gave it back.

567
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,060
 But what's the point?

568
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:39,860
 What did I feel in that moment

569
00:26:39,860 --> 00:26:41,940
 when I saw that number?

570
00:26:41,940 --> 00:26:42,780
 What did I feel?

571
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:45,380
 Immediate despair, right?

572
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:47,740
 (audience laughing)

573
00:26:47,740 --> 00:26:48,660
 This is it, babe.

574
00:26:48,660 --> 00:26:50,000
 We had a good run.

575
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,620
 (audience laughing)

576
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:53,260
 Yeah, I'll see you later, right?

577
00:26:53,260 --> 00:26:56,060
 Need?

578
00:26:56,060 --> 00:26:59,780
 Oh, no, right?

579
00:26:59,780 --> 00:27:03,620
 Those feelings crept up in me fast,

580
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:06,620
 and that's exactly what God is saying

581
00:27:06,620 --> 00:27:11,620
 is the posture of someone who he responds to and justifies.

582
00:27:11,620 --> 00:27:14,620
 Feel that.

583
00:27:14,620 --> 00:27:16,200
 That's the posture.

584
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:19,140
 And some of you guys,

585
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:23,300
 you are bankrupt spiritually,

586
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:27,180
 but you are acting like a millionaire

587
00:27:27,180 --> 00:27:32,580
 as if sort of putting on airs will impress God.

588
00:27:32,580 --> 00:27:36,580
 Listen, it doesn't impress him.

589
00:27:36,580 --> 00:27:40,760
 Need does, though.

590
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,660
 Need.

591
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:46,220
 Repent of that.

592
00:27:46,220 --> 00:27:47,860
 Come to him desperate for forgiveness

593
00:27:47,860 --> 00:27:50,560
 and watch him give it 'cause he loves to.

594
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:54,920
 We starting to see the theme?

595
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:58,460
 God's ear is bent toward the needy widow

596
00:27:58,460 --> 00:28:01,500
 and his heart is forgiving to the sinful tax collector

597
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:05,300
 and as if to drive his point home one more time,

598
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:07,220
 Luke gives us one more story.

599
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:09,180
 We're gonna look at it together.

600
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:11,220
 Verse 15 says this.

601
00:28:11,220 --> 00:28:16,200
 Now they were bringing even infants to him

602
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:18,180
 that he might touch them.

603
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:20,940
 And when the disciples saw it, they rebuked them,

604
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:23,580
 but Jesus called them to him saying,

605
00:28:23,580 --> 00:28:27,540
 "Let the children come to me and do not hinder them

606
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:30,720
 for to such belongs the kingdom of God.

607
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,620
 Truly I say to you,

608
00:28:32,620 --> 00:28:36,220
 whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child

609
00:28:36,220 --> 00:28:38,620
 shall not enter it."

610
00:28:38,620 --> 00:28:41,620
 Again, I just want you to feel this.

611
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:43,420
 This is another one of those moments

612
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:45,860
 where there's a disconnect here.

613
00:28:45,860 --> 00:28:48,900
 See, in ancient Jewish culture,

614
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:53,260
 children were not little bitty bundles of chunky joy, right?

615
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:54,900
 They were not, you didn't bounce them on your lap

616
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:56,420
 and pass them around.

617
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:58,340
 That's not what you did with a child.

618
00:28:58,340 --> 00:29:00,420
 They weren't little bundles of joy.

619
00:29:00,420 --> 00:29:03,520
 They were inconveniences then.

620
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,980
 Not because they were hated by people,

621
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:09,460
 but because in Jewish culture,

622
00:29:09,460 --> 00:29:12,820
 there was a high, high value placed on contribution.

623
00:29:12,820 --> 00:29:15,660
 What can you contribute to the family's good?

624
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:18,220
 If you can't contribute to the family's good yet,

625
00:29:18,220 --> 00:29:21,420
 then you're of low value to us until you can.

626
00:29:21,420 --> 00:29:24,000
 And so when they saw children back then,

627
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,600
 that was the sense that they got.

628
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:26,580
 It wasn't an endearing thing.

629
00:29:26,580 --> 00:29:29,660
 And for Jesus, somebody of Jesus's stature

630
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:34,660
 and notoriety to come around and to bless these infants

631
00:29:34,660 --> 00:29:37,460
 was beneath the teacher of his stature.

632
00:29:37,460 --> 00:29:38,300
 Do you see that?

633
00:29:38,300 --> 00:29:40,200
 It would have been a really surprising

634
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:43,300
 and even offensive sight for his disciples to see this.

635
00:29:43,300 --> 00:29:46,780
 That's why they rebuked those kids and those parents.

636
00:29:46,780 --> 00:29:51,780
 And yet here he is, Jesus, holding and blessing infants,

637
00:29:51,780 --> 00:29:55,420
 non-contributors, the vulnerable.

638
00:29:56,820 --> 00:29:59,820
 And one more time, we're faced with that question, aren't we?

639
00:29:59,820 --> 00:30:02,020
 How do we see ourselves?

640
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:04,260
 That's what his disciples were faced with in this moment.

641
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:07,020
 That's what Jesus is doing in this moment.

642
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:12,020
 Do you see yourself, be honest, when you think about you,

643
00:30:12,020 --> 00:30:15,580
 do you see yourself as strong,

644
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:21,860
 self-sustaining, important, substantial?

645
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:26,020
 Or is the first thought that you have

646
00:30:26,020 --> 00:30:31,020
 when you think about you, needy, dependent, trusting,

647
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:35,060
 vulnerable, without help?

648
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:39,940
 Truly, I say to you, whoever does not receive

649
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:44,580
 the kingdom of God like a child shall not enter it.

650
00:30:44,580 --> 00:30:46,020
 Let that sober you tonight.

651
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:49,820
 You feeling challenged?

652
00:30:49,820 --> 00:30:54,220
 These are our three scenes.

653
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:58,500
 These are our three role models.

654
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:03,500
 And this leaves us with some questions to answer.

