00:31:16,740 --> 00:31:18,500
 What do they teach us about prayer?

660
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:21,880
 Three ending observations.

661
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:25,580
 What does this mean for us?

662
00:31:25,580 --> 00:31:30,580
 Number one, your self-reliance will kill you.

663
00:31:30,580 --> 00:31:39,380
 Your self-reliance will kill you.

664
00:31:39,380 --> 00:31:47,660
 There's a lot of encouragement to be had in this passage,

665
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:51,260
 but this passage is also a warning tonight.

666
00:31:52,100 --> 00:31:57,100
 At the very center of Christianity is a concession

667
00:31:57,100 --> 00:32:03,020
 that I lack what I need to be right with God.

668
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:06,740
 That's at the heart of this thing.

669
00:32:06,740 --> 00:32:12,300
 That I lack the power to change things in me.

670
00:32:12,300 --> 00:32:16,460
 That I lack the power to change things around me.

671
00:32:16,460 --> 00:32:21,460
 So to act like you're strong or able or righteous

672
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:26,980
 or put together in and of yourself

673
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:31,980
 is not only anti-prayerful, it is anti-Christian.

674
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:40,700
 The Pharisee was a better man than the tax collector.

675
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:46,220
 Do you hear me?

676
00:32:46,220 --> 00:32:49,460
 No one would have disagreed with this.

677
00:32:49,460 --> 00:32:52,100
 He wasn't stealing from anybody.

678
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:57,100
 He was keeping the Torah as he knew how.

679
00:32:57,100 --> 00:33:00,900
 He wasn't committing adultery or cheating

680
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,180
 or doing these types of things.

681
00:33:02,180 --> 00:33:03,580
 He wasn't thieving.

682
00:33:03,580 --> 00:33:08,580
 He was being good, and he went to hell.

683
00:33:13,100 --> 00:33:17,020
 We don't say that in 2019 though, right?

684
00:33:17,020 --> 00:33:19,900
 We don't talk like that in 2019,

685
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:24,620
 'cause it's just not, it's better left unsaid, isn't it?

686
00:33:24,620 --> 00:33:28,620
 But do you see that's the point?

687
00:33:28,620 --> 00:33:33,180
 The good guy loses in that story.

688
00:33:33,180 --> 00:33:35,340
 And the bad guy, the degenerate,

689
00:33:35,340 --> 00:33:37,940
 the one who owned his need and could come to God

690
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:42,620
 with all of his bankruptcy, he's the one God justified.

691
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:45,300
 The cannibal.

692
00:33:45,300 --> 00:33:53,140
 You having it all figured out before you come to God,

693
00:33:53,140 --> 00:33:57,180
 guys, girls, it's working against you.

694
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:59,940
 It's working against you.

695
00:33:59,940 --> 00:34:04,780
 Your efforts to be put together and morally pristine

696
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:07,660
 so that God will accept you,

697
00:34:07,660 --> 00:34:12,060
 those things are working against you tonight.

698
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:13,620
 It's not good for you.

699
00:34:13,620 --> 00:34:17,780
 Some of you tonight, you're hearing this,

700
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:22,780
 and what you need to do is lay down your trust in you

