00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:31,300
 And when God contributes everything else,

724
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:34,380
 who is the one that in the end I get to brag on

725
00:35:34,380 --> 00:35:36,020
 as having done something good?

726
00:35:36,020 --> 00:35:38,940
 Who is the one at the end that I can point at

727
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:41,180
 and celebrate and say, "That's praiseworthy"?

728
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:44,300
 I'm not allowed to point at me anymore.

729
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:49,300
 If he made the contribution, I can only point at him.

730
00:35:49,300 --> 00:35:52,020
 This is Christianity.

731
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:54,340
 If you're wondering what this whole thing was,

732
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:55,700
 maybe you're here for one of the first times,

733
00:35:55,700 --> 00:35:57,620
 you're just trying to sort out

734
00:35:57,620 --> 00:36:00,740
 what this Christian thing is, this is it.

735
00:36:00,740 --> 00:36:02,500
 This is the gospel.

736
00:36:02,500 --> 00:36:05,660
 You and I rebelled against God.

737
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:07,140
 Our first parents did it,

738
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:08,980
 and we learned a good lesson from them.

739
00:36:08,980 --> 00:36:10,420
 We keep on doing it, don't we?

740
00:36:10,420 --> 00:36:12,780
 We stiff on him at every turn.

741
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:16,660
 And God in his mercy, instead of leaving us, he pursued us.

742
00:36:16,660 --> 00:36:20,860
 He condescended to come get us in the person of Jesus.

743
00:36:20,860 --> 00:36:22,260
 Jesus lived the perfect life.

744
00:36:22,260 --> 00:36:24,940
 You and I could never do in our place.

745
00:36:24,940 --> 00:36:26,900
 He made the contribution.

746
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:28,780
 He hung up on a Roman cross

747
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:30,900
 and bled out for six hours in our place.

748
00:36:30,900 --> 00:36:33,900
 His contribution, not ours, rose from the grave,

749
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:37,420
 defeated death, conquered all our enemies in our place.

750
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:38,780
 His contribution.

751
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:41,900
 In the end, every Christian will never be able

752
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:42,980
 to point at themselves.

753
00:36:42,980 --> 00:36:45,420
 If you're truly in Christ, the best we can do,

754
00:36:45,420 --> 00:36:47,700
 the greatest thing we can do is only point at the one

755
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:51,580
 who made the contribution, and that's Jesus every time.

756
00:36:51,580 --> 00:36:53,740
 That is the gospel.

757
00:36:53,740 --> 00:36:56,780
 We're needy, he is the need meter.

758
00:36:56,780 --> 00:36:58,300
 Do you see that?

759
00:36:58,300 --> 00:37:00,180
 And praise God for that.

760
00:37:00,180 --> 00:37:05,180
 And if that's true, if he's the strong one when I'm weak,

761
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:08,220
 if he's the powerful one when I'm not powerful,

762
00:37:08,220 --> 00:37:11,020
 if he's the contributor when my basket's empty

763
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:13,780
 and I have nothing to give to him, if that's true,

764
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:15,800
 then this last point is true.

765
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:21,060
 When things feel the most hopeless,

766
00:37:21,060 --> 00:37:24,260
 that's when there's the most hope.

767
00:37:24,260 --> 00:37:26,140
 That's when there's the most hope.

768
00:37:28,340 --> 00:37:31,140
 If what we've just seen from Luke is true,

769
00:37:31,140 --> 00:37:34,980
 our optimism, listen, your optimism in your prayer life

770
00:37:34,980 --> 00:37:38,620
 should be exploding if you feel like you're not bringing

